BEARMAN OF THE ICE WILDERNESS

Bearmen are massive, ursine humanoids native to the cold northern wilderness
regions.  They are among the most physically powerful of the OCC-eligible
races, with Supernatural Strength and Endurance well beyond most humanoids.
Their communities are isolationist but trade with human settlements on their
own terms.  The Coalition generally leaves them alone: attacking a Bearman
is rarely worth the casualties.

ATTRIBUTES (approximate ranges):
  IQ: 6-16   ME: 3-18   MA: 3-18   PS: 13-28 (Supernatural)
  PP: 3-18   PE: 13-28  PB: 2-12   Spd: 6-16

DAMAGE POOL:
  SDC: 3d6 x10 (approx 30-180)

SPECIAL ABILITIES:
  - Supernatural Physical Strength and Endurance (exceptional values)
  - Enhanced smell: track by scent
  - Hibernation: can survive extended periods without food in cold regions
  - Natural resilience to cold environments

PENALTIES:
  - Large size limits equipment options
  - Below average Spd compared to lighter races
  - D-Bee classification in Coalition territory

OCC ELIGIBLE: Yes.
ALIGNMENT: Any.

